    "text": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>2-4-110</b>\n</p><p>(Occulting) Hood\n</p><p>An opaque cover brought down over the light source in an optical apparatus to obscure it for a short period.\n</p><p>Most commonly used in occulting lights and in signalling projectors.\n</p><p><span class=\"mw-image-border\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:Ch2_Fig35.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/a/a2/Ch2_Fig35.jpg/400px-Ch2_Fig35.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"400\" height=\"203\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/a/a2/Ch2_Fig35.jpg/600px-Ch2_Fig35.jpg 1.5x, /wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/a/a2/Ch2_Fig35.jpg/800px-Ch2_Fig35.jpg 2x\"></a></span>\n</p><p><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<i>Please note that this is the term as it stands in the original <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> Dictionary edition (1970-1989)</i>\n<br>\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-d